prompt: approval process with four java variables, approver "java.lang.String", traveller "org.acme.travels.Traveller", firstLineApproval "java.lang.Boolean" and secondLineApproval "java.lang.Boolean". The process has two user tasks, the first one is called "First Line approval"-> and it is assigned to the actor "manager" and group "managers", has data input receives the traveller variable and has a two data outputs ActorId which targets to the approver variable and approved that targets to firstLineApproval. The second user task  is called "Second Line approval", it is assigned to the "managers" group and has two data inputs: ExcludedOwnerId which source is the approver variable and traveller which source is traveller. As an output it has approved that targets to the secondLineApproval variable.

prompt: proces with timer bound to a task. boundary timer event - used as an option to move process flow through alternative path after expiration time. This process has a delay string variable that holds an iso date expression. It starts with a script task that is connected to a user task called "User task 1", the task is connected to an end event. The task also has a bound timer, configured to be fired depending on the delay variable value. If the timer is fired the script task "After Timer" will be executed and the process will end in the "End" end event.->
